    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="834"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d834">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.20/5a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Ask that authority be cabled Consul General Lyon to sign, for Liberian Secretary
                    of War, after consultation with this Department, temporary contracts for one
                    year with former American Army officers, as follows: Major at two thousand
                    dollars and two captains at sixteen hundred dollars each per annum. Salaries to
                    commence when officers leave homes and to be paid by General Receiver. Actual
                    traveling expenses and free quarters allowed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
